To run the tests you'll need access to an Openstack Swift server.

Set these environment variables before running the tests

Swift Auth v1.0 :
  export OS_API_USER='user'
  export OS_API_KEY='key'
  export OS_AUTH_URL='https://url.of.auth.server/v1.0'

OpenStack Identity Service (Keystone) v2.0 :
  export ST_AUTH_VERSION=2.0
  export OS_USERNAME='user_name'
  export OS_PASSWORD='password'
  export OS_TENANT_NAME='tenant_name'
  export OS_AUTH_URL='https://url.of.auth.server/'

OpenStack Identity Service (Keystone) v3 :
  export ST_AUTH_VERSION=3
  export OS_USERNAME='user_name'
  export OS_PASSWORD='password'
  export OS_PROJECT_NAME='project_name'
  export OS_AUTH_URL='https://url.of.auth.server/'

And optionally :
  export OS_USER_DOMAIN_NAME='user_domain_name'
  export OS_PROJECT_DOMAIN_NAME='project_domain_name'
  export OS_REGION_NAME='region_name'

Tests require a recent version of paramiko, 2.0.x is recommended.

Those tests were based on ftp-cloudfs tests, MIT licensed.

Please check the original project at:

http://github.com/cloudfs/ftp-cloudfs

